Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Peel and slice the @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm thick rounds.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once boiling, add the potato slices to the water and simmer until just tender, ~{8-12%minutes}. Once cooked, reserve some of the potato water (see pantry for amount), then carefully drain in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, then add the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) pan used for the potatoes.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @reserved potato water{100%ml} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lay half the cooked potato slices into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Top with half the caramelised onion, then crumble over half the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g}. Pour over the creamy dauphinoise sauce.

Top with the remaining caramelised onion, Greek style salad cheese and hard Italian style cheese.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and bubbling, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Put the dish onto a baking tray to catch any drips.

== Apple and Pea Shoot Salad ==

In the meantime, quarter, core and thinly slice the @apple{1}(quartered and thinly sliced) (no need to peel).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @pea shoots{40%g} and apple to the dressing. Toss together.

When ready, share your balsamic onion dauphinoise between your plates.

Serve with the apple salad alongside.

Enjoy.